## When to use

- You need the result this interface computes or returns, and the live system is
  the source of truth for that answer.
- Reproducing the logic yourself would risk drifting from the real system.

## When NOT to use

- The endpoint is not reachable or you have no credentials. This skill calls a
  live service; it cannot answer offline.
- You only need static knowledge about the code — use a read-only repo map pack.

## How to call

The capability runs in a live system, so this pack ships a real caller:

```bash
{{ sample_command }}
```

- The endpoint and auth token come from the environment (`{{ endpoint_env }}`,
  `{{ token_env }}`). They are never hard-coded.
- The caller previews by default. It only sends a request when you pass
  `--execute` AND `{{ endpoint_env }}` is set. With `--dry-run`, or with no
  endpoint configured, it prints the exact request it would send and touches
  nothing.

